document_title: Premature birth: Causes, signs and how to care for your baby
subsection_content:
During pregnancy, if you have any of the following symptoms, you should contact a specialist for the fastest guidance and treatment:
Dull back pain;; The baby shows signs of pushing downward;; Swelling in hands, feet or face;; Nausea, vomiting or diarrhea;; Blurred vision or other eye disorders;; Abdominal cramps similar to menstrual cramps;; The baby moves little or stops moving;; Abnormal vaginal discharge or blood.
